Subject: wifi: ath12k: avoid duplicate SoC debugfs files

ath12k_core_start() already creates the SoC-level debugfs files after
powering up the device. Do not create the same files again from
ath12k_mac_allocate(), otherwise debugfs reports duplicate entries such
as "simulate_fw_crash" and "device_dp_stats".

Signed-off-by: Igor Kravchenko <igor.kravchenko05@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -14387,7 +14387,6 @@ int ath12k_mac_allocate(struct ath12k_hw
 		if (!ab)
 			continue;
 
-		ath12k_debugfs_pdev_create(ab);
 		ath12k_mac_set_device_defaults(ab);
 		total_radio += ab->num_radios;
 	}
